{"type":"message","id":"51147825","parentId":"348c7373","timestamp":"2026-03-23T21:36:31.033Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the OpenClaw Control UI. It's a full-featured dashboard with:\n\n1. **Navigation**: Left sidebar with sections like Chat, Agents, Config, Cron, Skills, Nodes, etc.\n2. **Top bar**: Status indicators, theme switcher, search, gateway status\n3. **Chat interface**: Full messaging UI with tool cards, markdown rendering, session controls\n4. **Config panel**: Full JSON editor with form-based config editing\n5. **Cron jobs**: Management UI for scheduled tasks\n6. **Agents**: Multi-agent routing interface\n7. **Skills**: Skill management\n\n\n8. **Nodes**: Device pairing and management\n9. **Logs**: Live log streaming with filtering\n10. **Themes**: Dark/light modes with accent color customization (OpenClaw red by default, teal for openknot, blue for dash)\n11. **Accessibility features**: Command palette, responsive mobile layout, glassmorphism effects, and smooth animations\n\nThe whole interface is built with CSS custom properties for theming, uses Inter and JetBrains Mono fonts, and has a very polished dark theme with a red accent that really stands out.","thinkingSignature":"8f0f8f5dc8e0d95871c556b662572ef9eda2701b2644ea83cf04bba2ca61010c"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's what the Nova/OpenClaw Control UI looks like based on the source:\n\n**Overall Structure:**\n- **Shell layout**: 258px collapsible nav sidebar + topbar (52px) + scrollable content area\n- **Dark theme by default** (`#0e1015` bg) with an optional light mode\n- **Fonts**: Inter (body) + JetBrains Mono (code)\n\n**Color Themes (4 built-in):**\n| Theme | Accent |\n|-------|--------|\n| Default | `#ff5c5c` (coral red) |\n| OpenKnot | `#14b8a6` (teal) |\n| Dash | `#3b82f6` (blue) |\n| Light | inverted palette |\n\n**Key UI Panels:**\n- **Chat** — Full messaging UI with streaming, tool call cards, markdown, copy buttons, TTS toggle\n- **Agents** — Multi-agent session management, model overrides, thinking/reasoning toggles, file editor\n- **Sessions** — List with thinking/fast/verbose overrides, last-run timestamps\n- **Cron** — Full CRUD for scheduled jobs, run history, staggered scheduling\n- **Config** — Dual-mode (form + raw JSON editor), diff view on changes, inline validation\n- **Skills** — Install, enable/disable, per-skill API key management\n- **Nodes** — Device pairing/approval for mobile\n- **Logs** — Live tail with level filters (trace → fatal)\n- **Command palette** — `Ctrl+K` quick nav to any section\n\n**Desktop polish:**\n- Glassmorphism topbar (backdrop blur)\n- Skeleton loading states\n- Toast notifications, exec approval overlays\n- Responsive: collapses nav to hamburger on mobile\n- Accent glow shadows, spring easing, view transitions\n\nIt's a genuinely well-built SPA — comparable to commercial SaaS dashboards. The gateway token auth is `05a9121e...` if you want to point a browser at `http://192.168.1.217:18789/` to try it live."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":55585,"output":671,"cacheRead":13925,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":70181,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774301771999}}
