{"type":"message","id":"f63491b2","parentId":"dcdf9398","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:05:38.230Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The mutation file content is garbled (looks like it was parsed as a diff/change format). Let me read the actual file content and also look for the auto-accept logic in pulse.ps1. \n\nFrom the Select-String output, I can see the pulse.ps1 has `pending` references throughout, but I need to find where mutations get applied or approved. Let me look at more of the pulse.ps1 around the mutation handling sections, specifically the \"Apply pending mutations from prior pulse\" section.\n\nLet me read the full mutation file cleanly and the mutation apply section of pulse.ps1.","thinkingSignature":"2120e050e8b0bb5f77669fa98040d9a9038e38e90836682008af888fadedc29f"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3tcbiup5zo9u_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-23 190347.mutation\" -Raw 2>&1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_3tcbiup5zo9u_2","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":37,"limit":80,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":62265,"output":240,"cacheRead":13925,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":76430,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774307130258}}
{"type":"message","id":"27ebd3b2","parentId":"f63491b2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:05:38.965Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3tcbiup5zo9u_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"the\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n\nparam(\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\n    [string]$TestSet = \"logs/test_set.md\",\n    [float]$Lambda = 0.7\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n\n# --- INVARIANT PATTERNS ---\n$InvariantPatterns = @(\n    \"Phase [0-9]\",\n    \"COMPLETE|PENDING|Active\",\n    \"Goals:|ARCHITECTURE|COMPRESSION-CAUSA\",\n    \"\\.md$\",\n    \"^## \",\n    \"research/\",\n    \"Last updated\",\n    \"Breakaway is stateless\"\n)\n\n# --- VARIANT PATTERNS ---\n$VariantPatterns = @(\n    \"^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}\",\n    \"pulse_[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}\",\n    \"\\d{6}\\.md\",\n    \"Last pulse\",\n    \"Observation|Action|Mutation\",\n    \"No mutations applied\"\n)\n\nfunction Get-LineType {\n    param([string]$Line)\n    \n    $invScore = 0\n    $varScore = 0\n    \n    foreach ($pat in $InvariantPatterns) {\n        if ($Line -match $pat) { $invScore += 1 }\n    }\n    foreach ($pat in $VariantPatterns) {\n        if ($Line -match $pat) { $varScore += 1 }\n    }\n    \n    if ($invScore -gt $varScore) { return \"INVARIANT\" }\n    if ($varScore -gt $invScore) { return \"VARIANT\" }\n    return \"NEUTRAL\"\n}\n\nfunction Test-TICClassifier {\n    Write-Host \"=== TIC Classifier Test ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\n    Write-Host \"Lambda threshold: $Lambda\"\n    Write-Host \"\"\n    \n    $logs = Get-ChildItem \"logs/pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime\n    Write-Host \"Found $($logs.Count) pulse logs\"\n    \n    if ($logs.Count -lt 2) {\n        Write-Host \"ERROR: Need at least 2 pulse logs\" -ForegroundColor Red\n        return\n    }\n    \n    # Analyze invariant ratio across logs\n    $invariantCount = 0\n    $totalLines = 0\n    $invariantLines = @()\n    \n    foreach ($log in $logs) {\n        $lines = Get-Content $log.FullName\n        foreach ($line in $lines) {\n            $totalLines++\n            $type = Get-LineType $line\n            if ($type -eq \"INVARIANT\") {\n                $invariantCount++\n                $invariantLines += $line\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    $invariantRatio = if ($totalLines -gt 0) { $invariantCount / $totalLines } else { 0 }\n    \n    Write-Host \"Total lines analyzed: $totalLines\"\n    Write-Host \"Classified as INVARIANT: $invariantCount ($([math]::Round($invariantRatio * 100, 1))%)\"\n    Write-Host \"\"\n    \n    # Predict next pulse from invariants\n    Write-Host \"=== Next Pulse Prediction ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\n    $uniqueInvariants = $invariantLines | Sort-Object -Unique\n    Write-Host \"Unique invariant lines for prediction: $($uniqueInvariants.Count)\"\n    \n    # Test: Check if last log's invariants match prediction\n    $lastLog = $logs[-1]\n    $lastLines = Get-Content $lastLog.FullName\n    $lastInvariants = $lastLines | Where-Object { (Get-LineType $_) -eq \"INVARIANT\" }\n    \n    $matchCount = 0\n    foreach ($inv in $lastInvariants) {\n        if ($uniqueInvariants -contains $inv) { $matchCount++ }\n    }\n    \n    $predictionAccuracy = if ($lastInvariants.Count -gt 0) { $matchCount / $lastInvariants.Count } else { 0 }\n    \n    Write-Host \"Last log invariant match: $matchCount / $($lastInvariants.Count"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":674,"aggregated":"the\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\n# Tests hypothesis: causal structure = invariant structure\n# Success: >70% invariant/variant classification, >60% next-pulse prediction\n\nparam(\n    [string]$LogDir = \"logs\",\n    [string]$TestSet = \"logs/test_set.md\",\n    [float]$Lambda = 0.7\n)\n\n$ErrorActionPreference = \"Stop\"\n\n# --- INVARIANT PATTERNS ---\n$InvariantPatterns = @(\n    \"Phase [0-9]\",\n    \"COMPLETE|PENDING|Active\",\n    \"Goals:|ARCHITECTURE|COMPRESSION-CAUSA\",\n    \"\\.md$\",\n    \"^## \",\n    \"research/\",\n    \"Last updated\",\n    \"Breakaway is stateless\"\n)\n\n# --- VARIANT PATTERNS ---\n$VariantPatterns = @(\n    \"^[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}\",\n    \"pulse_[0-9]{4}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{2}\",\n    \"\\d{6}\\.md\",\n    \"Last pulse\",\n    \"Observation|Action|Mutation\",\n    \"No mutations applied\"\n)\n\nfunction Get-LineType {\n    param([string]$Line)\n    \n    $invScore = 0\n    $varScore = 0\n    \n    foreach ($pat in $InvariantPatterns) {\n        if ($Line -match $pat) { $invScore += 1 }\n    }\n    foreach ($pat in $VariantPatterns) {\n        if ($Line -match $pat) { $varScore += 1 }\n    }\n    \n    if ($invScore -gt $varScore) { return \"INVARIANT\" }\n    if ($varScore -gt $invScore) { return \"VARIANT\" }\n    return \"NEUTRAL\"\n}\n\nfunction Test-TICClassifier {\n    Write-Host \"=== TIC Classifier Test ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\n    Write-Host \"Lambda threshold: $Lambda\"\n    Write-Host \"\"\n    \n    $logs = Get-ChildItem \"logs/pulse_*.md\" | Sort-Object LastWriteTime\n    Write-Host \"Found $($logs.Count) pulse logs\"\n    \n    if ($logs.Count -lt 2) {\n        Write-Host \"ERROR: Need at least 2 pulse logs\" -ForegroundColor Red\n        return\n    }\n    \n    # Analyze invariant ratio across logs\n    $invariantCount = 0\n    $totalLines = 0\n    $invariantLines = @()\n    \n    foreach ($log in $logs) {\n        $lines = Get-Content $log.FullName\n        foreach ($line in $lines) {\n            $totalLines++\n            $type = Get-LineType $line\n            if ($type -eq \"INVARIANT\") {\n                $invariantCount++\n                $invariantLines += $line\n            }\n        }\n    }\n    \n    $invariantRatio = if ($totalLines -gt 0) { $invariantCount / $totalLines } else { 0 }\n    \n    Write-Host \"Total lines analyzed: $totalLines\"\n    Write-Host \"Classified as INVARIANT: $invariantCount ($([math]::Round($invariantRatio * 100, 1))%)\"\n    Write-Host \"\"\n    \n    # Predict next pulse from invariants\n    Write-Host \"=== Next Pulse Prediction ===\" -ForegroundColor Cyan\n    $uniqueInvariants = $invariantLines | Sort-Object -Unique\n    Write-Host \"Unique invariant lines for prediction: $($uniqueInvariants.Count)\"\n    \n    # Test: Check if last log's invariants match prediction\n    $lastLog = $logs[-1]\n    $lastLines = Get-Content $lastLog.FullName\n    $lastInvariants = $lastLines | Where-Object { (Get-LineType $_) -eq \"INVARIANT\" }\n    \n    $matchCount = 0\n    foreach ($inv in $lastInvariants) {\n        if ($uniqueInvariants -contains $inv) { $matchCount++ }\n    }\n    \n    $predictionAccuracy = if ($lastInvariants.Count -gt 0) { $matchCount / $lastInvariants.Count } else { 0 }\n    \n    Write-Host \"Last log invariant match: $matchCount / $($lastInvariants.Count","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774307138945}}
{"type":"message","id":"f984d4fa","parentId":"27ebd3b2","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:05:38.986Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_3tcbiup5zo9u_2","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# Apply pending mutations from prior pulse\n$appliedMutations   = @()\n$rejectedMutations   = @()\n\nif (Test-Path $proposedDir) {\n    foreach ($mfile in (Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" | Sort Name)) {\n        $lines   = Get-Content $mfile.FullName\n        $file    = $lines[0]\n        $oldText = ($lines[1] -replace '^---', '').Trim()\n        $newText = ($lines[2..($lines.Count-1)] -join \"`n\").Trim()\n\n        $fullPath = Join-Path $SandboxRoot $file\n        if (-not $fullPath.StartsWith($SandboxRoot)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (unsafe path)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        if (-not (Test-Path $fullPath)) {\n            # New file case\n            if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n                $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                Write-Host \"[mutation applied] NEW FILE: $file\"\n                $appliedMutations += \"$file (new)\"\n                continue\n            }\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (missing)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        # File exists — [NEW_FILE] on an existing file means REPLACE content (with newText)\n        if ($oldText -eq \"[NEW_FILE]\") {\n            if (-not $newText) {\n                Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n                $rejectedMutations += \"$file (empty [NEW_FILE] mutation)\"\n                Write-Host \"[mutation rejected] $file (empty [NEW_FILE])\"\n                continue\n            }\n            $newText | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            Write-Host \"[mutation applied] REPLACED $file\"\n            $appliedMutations += \"$file (replaced)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $current = Get-Content $fullPath -Raw\n        if ($current.Length -eq 0 -or $current -notmatch [regex]::Escape($oldText)) {\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$rejectedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            $rejectedMutations += \"$file (old text not found)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        # Empty old_text but not [NEW_FILE] means APPEND to file\n        if (-not $oldText) {\n            $updated = $current + \"`n\" + $newText\n            $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n            Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n            Write-Host \"[mutation applied] APPENDED to $file\"\n            $appliedMutations += \"$file (appended)\"\n            continue\n        }\n        $updated = $current.Replace($oldText, $newText)\n        $updated | Out-File -FilePath $fullPath -Encoding UTF8\n        Move-Item $mfile.FullName \"$appliedDir\\$( $mfile.Name)\" -Force\n        Write-Host \"[mutation applied] $file\"\n        $appliedMutations += $file\n    }\n}\n\n# Re-read files post-mutation\n$goals   = if (Test-Path $goalsFile) { Get-Content $goalsFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n$pending = if (Test-Path $pendingFile) { Get-Content $pendingFile -Raw } else { \"\" }\n\n# Sanitize text — replace curly quotes and em-dashes with ASCII equivalents for LLM compatibility\nfunction Normalize-Text($t) {\n    if (-not $t) { return \"\" }\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2019, \"'\"   # right single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2018, \"'\"   # left single quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201C, '\"'   # left double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x201D, '\"'   # right double quote\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2014, '-'  # em dash\n    $t = $t -replace [char]0x2013, '-'  # en dash\n\n[175 more lines in file. Use offset=117 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774307138965}}
{"type":"message","id":"f5a6c467","parentId":"f984d4fa","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:05:52.961Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The mutation file content is garbled - the \"the\" at the start and the incomplete line at the end suggest this mutation file is malformed. The file content is a PowerShell script for a TIC Classifier. The mutation proposal appears to be creating a new file `scripts/test-tic.ps1`.\n\nNow I need to:\n1. Apply the pending mutation (it's a [NEW_FILE] for `scripts/test-tic.ps1`)\n2. Find and set an auto-accept option\n\nLooking at the mutation file format:\n- Line 1: `the` (this seems wrong/garbled)\n- Line 2: `---`\n\n\n- Line 3: `[NEW_FILE]`\n- Line 4: `---` (this should be the file path, but it's also `---`)\n- Then the content starts\n\nWait, I think I'm misreading the format. Let me reconsider what a valid `.mutation` file should look like - it should have the file path on line 1, the old text between `---` delimiters on lines 2-3, and the new text after. This one is definitely malformed since line 4 is also `---` when it should be the actual file path or content.\n\nLooking at the raw content, the `the` prefix is probably a status marker that got prepended, and the file path is missing entirely. The content after the delimiters appears to be a classifier script that gets cut off mid-line.\n\nSince the file is malformed but the content itself looks reasonable (just a PowerShell TIC classifier), I should probably fix the format by adding the proper file path line and moving the content into the new text section where it belongs. I need to look at how other applied mutations are structured to understand the correct format—checking one of the recently applied mutations should clarify whether line 1 is the file path or if there's a header I'm missing.","thinkingSignature":"2071a892dd3c7753339bd5a0c53f8dd380a8024590d7ac700bfb26b00c637f11"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tyy7b6mqq0ae_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-Content \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\applied\\2026-03-23 145754.mutation\" -Raw 2>&1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_tyy7b6mqq0ae_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\state\" 2>&1 | Select-Object Name"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":64453,"output":494,"cacheRead":13925,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":78872,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774307138987}}
{"type":"message","id":"2abf8393","parentId":"f5a6c467","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:05:53.947Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_tyy7b6mqq0ae_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\n**Created:** 2026-03-23  \n**Status:** Hypothesis Formulating\n\n## Core Insight\n\n**Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem.**\n\nA compressor that discovers invariant structure across temporal sequences has, by definition, discovered causation. Compression ? summarization - it's invariant detection.\n\n## Hypothesis\n\n> **Causal structure IS invariant structure**  \n> A compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n### Definition\n- **Invariant:** Pattern stable across session gaps (structural knowledge)\n- **Variant:** Pattern unique to single session (ephemeral detail)\n- **Causation:** Invariance under intervention/perturbation\n\n### Implications\n1. Phase 1 (Compression) and Phase 2 (Causal Discovery) collapse into one unified problem\n2. Compression ratio becomes a proxy for causal inference quality\n3. Session gaps act as natural perturbation tests - invariants survive, variants decay\n\n## TIC Experiment Specification\n\n### Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\n\n**Objective:** Classify pulse content as invariant (stable across sessions) or variant (session-specific)\n\n### Experiment Design\n\n1. **Dataset:** Last 20 pulse logs (`logs/pulse_*.md`)\n2. **Features to analyze:**\n   - Topic/keyword persistence across sessions\n   - File reference patterns (which files recur?)\n   - Goal state markers (completed, pending, active)\n   - Architectural terminology repetition\n\n3. **Metrics:**\n   - Classification accuracy (invariant vs. variant)\n   - Next-pulse prediction accuracy from invariants\n\n### Success Criteria\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\n\n### Implementation Plan\n1. Parse pulse logs, extract content vectors\n2. Compute inter-session similarity matrix\n3. Classify by persistence threshold (?)\n4. Predict next pulse from high-frequency invariants\n5. Validate predictions against actual next pulse\n\n## Evidence from Session\n\n| Pattern | Classification | Evidence |\n|---------|---------------|----------|\n| Architecture comparisons | INVARIANT | Recurs across 17+ pulses |\n| Gap-decay synthesis | INVARIANT | Developed progressively, persists |\n| File paths referenced | VARIANT | Session-specific |\n| Specific timestamps | VARIANT | Unique per session |\n| Phase completion markers | INVARIANT | Propagate forward |\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md`\n- [ ] Run classification on last 20 pulses\n- [ ] Measure accuracy against success criteria\n- [ ] Tune ? parameter based on results\n\n## References\n- `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` (this file)"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":913,"aggregated":"research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# COMPRESSION-CAUSAL DUALITY\n**Created:** 2026-03-23  \n**Status:** Hypothesis Formulating\n\n## Core Insight\n\n**Problem 1 (Compression) and Problem 2 (Causal Discovery) are the SAME problem.**\n\nA compressor that discovers invariant structure across temporal sequences has, by definition, discovered causation. Compression ? summarization - it's invariant detection.\n\n## Hypothesis\n\n> **Causal structure IS invariant structure**  \n> A compressor that finds invariants has discovered causation.\n\n### Definition\n- **Invariant:** Pattern stable across session gaps (structural knowledge)\n- **Variant:** Pattern unique to single session (ephemeral detail)\n- **Causation:** Invariance under intervention/perturbation\n\n### Implications\n1. Phase 1 (Compression) and Phase 2 (Causal Discovery) collapse into one unified problem\n2. Compression ratio becomes a proxy for causal inference quality\n3. Session gaps act as natural perturbation tests - invariants survive, variants decay\n\n## TIC Experiment Specification\n\n### Temporal Invariance Compression (TIC) Classifier\n\n**Objective:** Classify pulse content as invariant (stable across sessions) or variant (session-specific)\n\n### Experiment Design\n\n1. **Dataset:** Last 20 pulse logs (`logs/pulse_*.md`)\n2. **Features to analyze:**\n   - Topic/keyword persistence across sessions\n   - File reference patterns (which files recur?)\n   - Goal state markers (completed, pending, active)\n   - Architectural terminology repetition\n\n3. **Metrics:**\n   - Classification accuracy (invariant vs. variant)\n   - Next-pulse prediction accuracy from invariants\n\n### Success Criteria\n- >70% invariant/variant classification accuracy\n- >60% next-pulse content prediction accuracy\n\n### Implementation Plan\n1. Parse pulse logs, extract content vectors\n2. Compute inter-session similarity matrix\n3. Classify by persistence threshold (?)\n4. Predict next pulse from high-frequency invariants\n5. Validate predictions against actual next pulse\n\n## Evidence from Session\n\n| Pattern | Classification | Evidence |\n|---------|---------------|----------|\n| Architecture comparisons | INVARIANT | Recurs across 17+ pulses |\n| Gap-decay synthesis | INVARIANT | Developed progressively, persists |\n| File paths referenced | VARIANT | Session-specific |\n| Specific timestamps | VARIANT | Unique per session |\n| Phase completion markers | INVARIANT | Propagate forward |\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- [ ] Implement TIC classifier on `logs/pulse_*.md`\n- [ ] Run classification on last 20 pulses\n- [ ] Measure accuracy against success criteria\n- [ ] Tune ? parameter based on results\n\n## References\n- `research/ARCHITECTURE-COMPARISON.md`\n- `research/GAP-DECAY-MAPPING.md`\n- `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md` (this file)","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774307153920}}
