{"type":"message","id":"78526aeb","parentId":"b404a773","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:06:03.985Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I understand the mutation file format:\n- Line 1: file path (e.g., `research/COMPRESSION-CAUSAL-DUALITY.md`)\n- Line 2: `---`\n- Line 3: old text or `[NEW_FILE]`\n- Line 4: `---`\n- Line 5+: new content\n\nThe pending mutation `2026-03-23 190347.mutation` has:\n```\nthe\n---\n[NEW_FILE]\n---\n# TIC Classifier - Temporal Invariance Compression\n...\n```\n\nSo the file path should be `the` which is clearly wrong. It looks like the LLM proposed a mutation for a new file but the file name got garbled. The content is a test script `scripts/test-tic.ps1`. \n \nI need to fix the mutation file by correcting the malformed file path—changing `the` to `scripts/test-tic.ps1`—then execute the pending mutations from the proposed folder and look for an auto-accept configuration option in pulse.ps1.","thinkingSignature":"dbebeaf66b4d48fcc6e25fb16672626319f4e1cf01523cd05c25d9c29abff91a"},{"type":"text","text":"Got it. The mutation file has a garbled filename (`the` instead of `scripts/test-tic.ps1`). I'll fix it, apply it, and add auto-accept to the pulse script.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k813mv1ygsfw_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\scripts\" 2>&1 | Select-Object Name"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_k813mv1ygsfw_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"$f = \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\mutations\\proposed\\2026-03-23 190347.mutation\"; $c = Get-Content $f -Raw; $c.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(50, $c.Length)) 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":65598,"output":386,"cacheRead":13925,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":79909,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774307154456}}
