{"type":"message","id":"1ce55691","parentId":"bd8ae192","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:09:02.673Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: [2026-03-23 19:07:18 EDT] Exec completed (vivid-ke, code 1) :: e... [plugins] [LinkMindPlugin] Context Engine factory registered via registerContextEngine(id, factory) [31;1mgateway connect failed: Error: gateway closed (1000): [0m [31;1mErro…\n\nNote: The previous agent run was aborted by the user. Resume carefully or ask for clarification.\n\nConversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"589\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-23 19:09 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\nis the whole mutation loop 1: Able to be mutated itself to improve or build on it and 2: automated? do i ever need to say yes when yoi ask if /i want you to apply mutations or does it happen next pulse?"}],"timestamp":1774307342665}}
{"type":"message","id":"ff08a0f3","parentId":"1ce55691","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:09:19.699Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Zach is asking two questions:\n1. Can the mutation loop itself be mutated/improved?\n2. Is it fully automated - does he ever need to say \"yes\" to apply mutations?\n\nLet me think about what I know:\n\n1. The mutation loop is in `pulse.ps1`. The sandbox can propose mutations to any file, including `pulse.ps1` itself. So yes, it can mutate itself.\n\n2. Looking at the pulse.ps1 code I read - it applies pending mutations from the `proposed` directory at the start of each pulse. There's no manual approval step in the script itself. The mutations flow is:\n   - Pulse runs → applies pending mutations from `proposed/` → does reasoning → proposes new mutations → logs → exits\n   - Next pulse → applies those mutations that were just proposed\n   - There's no user prompt or approval in the pulse.ps1 flow itself. But I added an `$AutoAccept` switch that defaults to `$false`. The cron job that triggers the pulse likely calls it without `-AutoAccept`, so it might not be fully automated yet.\n   - Looking at the state files, there's a `pending_actions.md` that the LLM uses to surface what needs attention. The mutation files in `proposed/` are separate from this pending actions concept - the pulse reads pending actions as informational context for the LLM, while the actual mutations in `proposed/` get applied automatically at the start of each pulse run.\n\nThe mutations are stored in `proposed/` directory and applied automatically when the next pulse executes - there's no manual approval step required. So when I suggested adding auto-accept functionality, I need to check whether that switch actually gets used in the current cron trigger, or if it's just an unused parameter I added.","thinkingSignature":"3845ceb581924b43d565da92b441390ae4935373eec86b5fdcb977e7f7ad4dee"},{"type":"text","text":"Good questions. Let me check the cron setup to confirm how the pulse is actually triggered.\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iuwj79cyldrv_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ScheduledTask -TaskPath \"\\OpenClaw\\\" 2>$null; Get-ScheduledTask 2>$null | Where-Object {$_.TaskName -like \"*pulse*\" -or $_.TaskName -like \"*sandbox*\" -or $_.TaskName -like \"*Sandbox*\"} | Select-Object TaskName, State, TaskPath 2>&1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_iuwj79cyldrv_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"schtasks /query /fo csv /v 2>$null | Select-String \"pulse\\|sandbox\\|Sandbox\" 2>&1 | Select -First 10"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":43,"output":537,"cacheRead":13925,"cacheWrite":68817,"totalTokens":83322,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774307342670}}
