{"type":"message","id":"975a7754","parentId":"8b352b05","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:09:39.759Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8epzusa5g4bc_2","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[32;1mTaskName          [0m[32;1m LastRunTime          [0m[32;1m NextRunTime[0m[32;1m LastTaskResult[0m\r\n[32;1m--------          [0m [32;1m-----------          [0m [32;1m-----------[0m [32;1m--------------[0m\r\nNova-Sandbox-Pulse 3/22/2026 10:45:28 PM                          0\r\npowershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1\""}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":2853,"aggregated":"[32;1mTaskName          [0m[32;1m LastRunTime          [0m[32;1m NextRunTime[0m[32;1m LastTaskResult[0m\r\n[32;1m--------          [0m [32;1m-----------          [0m [32;1m-----------[0m [32;1m--------------[0m\r\nNova-Sandbox-Pulse 3/22/2026 10:45:28 PM                          0\r\npowershell.exe -ExecutionPolicy Bypass -File \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1\"","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774307379719}}
{"type":"message","id":"29b80b9b","parentId":"975a7754","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:09:55.473Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Both tasks call pulse.ps1 without `-AutoAccept`. So my addition of the switch doesn't affect the automated behavior yet since the default is `$false`. \n\nNow let me answer Zach's questions:\n\n1. **Can the mutation loop mutate itself?** Yes — the sandbox can propose changes to `pulse.ps1`. The next pulse would then apply those changes. The mutation I just applied (test-tic.ps1) was a NEW file, not a mutation to pulse.ps1 itself.\n\n2. **Is it fully automated?** Yes — mutations in `proposed/` are applied automatically at the start of the next pulse run. There is NO manual approval step. The cron calls pulse.ps1 → pulse.ps1 applies all pending mutations → does reasoning → proposes new mutations → logs → exits. \n\nZach never gets asked \"do you want to apply this?\" — it happens automatically every 30 minutes (or whatever the schedule is). The `$AutoAccept` switch I added defaults to `$false`, which means it's not even being used by the cron jobs right now. The whole system runs on a propose-then-auto-apply cycle: the sandbox proposes a mutation, stores it in `proposed/`, and the next pulse execution automatically applies it without any human intervention.","thinkingSignature":"cde3c00f9792b79112eb5c861c4bc415588fc393338053595937e87d362f55fa"},{"type":"text","text":"Here's how it actually works:\n\n**1. Yes — the mutation system can mutate itself.** `pulse.ps1` is just a file in the sandbox. The LLM can propose changes to it and the next pulse will apply them. Same with any other file — cron configs, the parse_mutation.py script, everything.\n\n**2. It's fully automated. You never get asked.** The flow:\n\n```\ncron trigger (every 30 min)\n  → pulse.ps1 starts\n  → [applies ALL mutations from proposed/ directory automatically]\n  → reads goals + state\n  → LLM reasons\n  → proposes NEW mutations → writes to proposed/\n  → logs pulse_*.md\n  → exits\nnext cron trigger (30 min later)\n  → applies those new mutations automatically\n  → ...\n```\n\nThere's no approval prompt anywhere. `proposed/` → next pulse → `applied/` → repeat.\n\nThe `$AutoAccept` switch I added is actually a no-op right now — the cron calls `pulse.ps1` without it, and even if it were passed it wouldn't change behavior since the script already auto-applies everything. I added it as a placeholder in case you ever wanted a dry-run mode (`-AutoAccept:$false` to skip applying), but that's not how it works today.\n\nSo to answer your actual question: **no, you never need to say yes**. It all happens on the next pulse. The pending mutation you had (`test-tic.ps1`) was sitting in `proposed/` and would've been applied automatically the next time the cron fired."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":70004,"output":582,"cacheRead":13925,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84511,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774307379763}}
{"type":"message","id":"0fc44d3f","parentId":"29b80b9b","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:12:04.782Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Conversation info (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"message_id\": \"594\",\n  \"sender_id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"sender\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"Mon 2026-03-23 19:12 EDT\"\n}\n```\n\nSender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"Ton0Fun (8371302588)\",\n  \"id\": \"8371302588\",\n  \"name\": \"Ton0Fun\",\n  \"username\": \"Ton0Fun\"\n}\n```\n\nolay can you make it so it doesnt ask in the pulse summary message? or maybe have it tell me it will do it next pulse please? also can you look on my pc and remove whateverr is left of phpstorm"}],"timestamp":1774307524778}}
{"type":"message","id":"752b99be","parentId":"0fc44d3f","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:12:17.349Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Two requests:\n1. Make the pulse script not ask in the summary message, or have it say \"will apply next pulse\" instead of prompting\n2. Remove PHPStorm from the PC\n\nLet me first find the LLM prompt/summary section in pulse.ps1, then search for PHPStorm.","thinkingSignature":"4ecd4944352b4d0beab12be084f821c2c606bd0904033a7a9820537d023f4533"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8zkf582d72lv_1","name":"read","arguments":{"offset":200,"limit":80,"file_path":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\sandbox\\pulse.ps1"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8zkf582d72lv_2","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Program Files\\JetBrains\\PyCharm*\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue 2>&1 | Select-Object Name, FullName, InstallLocation; Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Program Files\\*\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue 2>&1 | Where-Object {$_.Name -like \"*php*\"} | Select-Object Name, FullName"}},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_8zkf582d72lv_3","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"Get-ChildItem \"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\AppData\\Local\\Programs\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue 2>&1 | Where-Object {$_.Name -like \"*PhpStorm*\" -or $_.Name -like \"*PHPStorm*\" -or $_.Name -like \"*phpstorm*\"} | Select-Object Name, FullName"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":0,"output":305,"cacheRead":84018,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":84323,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774307524780}}
{"type":"message","id":"3cada3e5","parentId":"752b99be","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:12:18.153Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_8zkf582d72lv_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"if ($mStart -ge 0) {\n    $responseFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_response.txt\"\n    $parsePy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"parse_mutation.py\"\n    $pythonExe = (Get-Command python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Source\n    if (-not $pythonExe) { $pythonExe = \"python\" }\n\n    $psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n    $psi.FileName = $pythonExe\n    $psi.Arguments = \"`\"$parsePy`\" `\"$responseFile`\"\"\n    $psi.WorkingDirectory = $SandboxRoot\n    $psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n    $psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n    $psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n    $psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n    $proc = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\n    $stdout = $proc.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n    $stderr = $proc.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n    $proc.WaitForExit()\n\n    # Read parsed result from JSON file\n    $resultFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".mutation_parse_result.json\"\n    if (Test-Path $resultFile) {\n        try {\n            $parseResult = Get-Content $resultFile -Raw -Encoding UTF8 | ConvertFrom-Json\n            $oldLine = $parseResult.old\n            $newText = $parseResult.new\n            $fileLine = $parseResult.file\n            Write-Host \"[mutation parsed via Python] old='$($oldLine.Substring(0, [Math]::Min(30, $oldLine.Length)))' file='$fileLine' new_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n        } catch {\n            Write-Host \"[mutation JSON parse error] $_\"\n        }\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed via Python] stderr: $stderr\"\n    }\n\n    # Fallback: infer file from ACTION block if not found\n    if (-not $fileLine) {\n        $actionMatch = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### ACTION\\s*\\n(.+?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n        if ($actionMatch.Success) {\n            $actionText = $actionMatch.Groups[1].Value\n            $fileInference = [regex]::Match($actionText, '(?:Create|Edit|Update|New file)[:\\s]+(?:`([^`]+)`|([^\\s`]+))')\n            if ($fileInference.Success) {\n                $fileLine = if ($fileInference.Groups[2].Value) { $fileInference.Groups[2].Value } else { $fileInference.Groups[1].Value }\n                Write-Host \"[file inferred from ACTION] $fileLine\"\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    if ($oldLine -and $fileLine -and $newText) {\n        $isNewFile = ($oldLine.Trim() -eq \"(new file)\")\n        $mutationContent = \"$fileLine`n---`n$(if($isNewFile) { '[NEW_FILE]' } else { $oldLine })`n---`n$newText\"\n        $mutationFile = Join-Path $proposedDir \"$timestamp.mutation\"\n        $mutationContent | Out-File -FilePath $mutationFile -Encoding UTF8\n        Write-Host \"[mutation proposed] $fileLine\"\n        $mutationProposed = $true\n    } else {\n        Write-Host \"[mutation parse failed] old='$oldLine' file='$fileLine' new_len=$($newText.Length)\"\n    }\n}\n\n# Parse OBSERVATION\n$obsMatch    = [regex]::Match($llmResponse, '(?s)### OBSERVATION\\s*\\n(.*?)(?:\\n###|\\nMUTATION)')\n$observation = if ($obsMatch.Success) { $obsMatch.Groups[1].Value.Trim() } else { \"Cycle complete.\" }\n\n# Write pulse log\n@\"\n# Pulse: $timestamp\n\n## Applied Mutations\n$appliedInfo\n$(if($rejectedMutations.Count -gt 0) { \"Rejected: \" + ($rejectedMutations -join '; ') } else { \"\" })\n\n## LLM Response\n$llmResponse\n\n## For Next Instantiation\n- Proposed mutations waiting: $((Get-ChildItem $proposedDir -Filter \"*.mutation\" -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue | Measure).Count)\n- Completed at: $(Get-Date -Format \"yyyy-MM-dd HH:mm:ss\")\n\"@ | Out-File -FilePath $logFile -Encoding UTF8\n\n\n[13 more lines in file. Use offset=280 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774307538126}}
