{"type":"message","id":"0083f19c","parentId":"1cd083e7","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:12:47.215Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_txvidhconjxm_1","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\nRecent: $recentPulseSummary\n\n$appliedInfo\n\nReply with exactly this format at the end. IMPORTANT: you MUST include the file: line in MUTATION - it is required.\n\n### OBSERVATION\n[1-2 sentence observation]\n\n### ACTION\n[Describe the file edit concisely]\n\n### MUTATION\nUse TRIPLE backticks (```) around the mutation block, NOT single backticks.\n```\nold_text: [exact text to find - or (new file) if creating new file]\nnew_text: [replacement text - keep it concise, a few lines max]\nfile: [required - relative path from sandbox root, e.g. research/my-doc.md or state/goals.md]\n```\n\"\n\n$promptText | Out-File -FilePath $promptFile -Encoding UTF8 -NoNewline\n\n$llmPy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"call_llm.py\"\n$pythonExe = (Get-Command python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Source\nif (-not $pythonExe) { $pythonExe = \"python\" }\n$psi = New-Object System.Diagnostics.ProcessStartInfo\n$psi.FileName = $pythonExe\n$psi.Arguments = \"`\"$llmPy`\" `\"$promptFile`\"\"\n$psi.WorkingDirectory = $SandboxRoot\n$psi.RedirectStandardOutput = $true\n$psi.RedirectStandardError = $true\n$psi.UseShellExecute = $false\n$psi.CreateNoWindow = $true\n$proc = [System.Diagnostics.Process]::Start($psi)\n$stdout = $proc.StandardOutput.ReadToEnd()\n$stderr = $proc.StandardError.ReadToEnd()\n$proc.WaitForExit()\n\n# Read response from file (written by Python, avoids console encoding issues)\n$responseFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_response.txt\"\nStart-Sleep -Milliseconds 500  # give Python time to write\nif (Test-Path $responseFile) {\n    $llmResponse = Get-Content $responseFile -Raw -Encoding UTF8\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] response length: $($llmResponse.Length)\"\n} else {\n    $llmResponse = \"[LLM error: no response file]\"\n    Write-Host \"[LLM] no response file found\"\n}\n\n# Parse MUTATION block — use Python for robust field extraction\n$mutationProposed = $false\n$oldLine = \"\"; $newText = \"\"; $fileLine = \"\"\n$mStart = $llmResponse.IndexOf('### MUTATION')\nif ($mStart -ge 0) {\n    $responseFile = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \".llm_response.txt\"\n    $parsePy = Join-Path $SandboxRoot \"parse_mutation.py\"\n    $pythonExe = (Get-Command python -ErrorAction SilentlyContinue).Source\n    if (-not $pythonExe) { $pythonExe = \"python\" }\n\n[88 more lines in file. Use offset=205 to continue.]"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774307567197}}
