{"type":"message","id":"6d98e9c9","parentId":"e4f5c5ed","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:45:11.940Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_x2cck6bjp1e4_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom typing import List\r\n\r\nN_GENUINE = 20; EPISODE_LENGTH = 170; QUERY_START = 150\r\nIGNORE_INDEX = -100\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass Episode:\r\n    input_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    oracle_actions: List[str]\r\n    target_value_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    genuine_keys: List[int] = None\r\n    genuine_values: List[int] = None\r\n\r\ndef generate_episode(seed=0):\r\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\r\n    gk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    gv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    fk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n    fv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n\r\n    inp, ora = [], []\r\n    # Encode: 100 steps (50 key+value pairs)\r\n    for i in range(100):\r\n        if i % 2 == 0:\r\n            inp.append(gk[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fk[i//2])\r\n            ora.append('PERCEIVE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\r\n        else:\r\n            inp.append(gv[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fv[i//2])\r\n            ora.append('WRITE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\r\n    # Delay: 50 steps\r\n    for _ in range(50):\r\n        inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49)); ora.append('SKIP')\r\n    # Query: 20 steps\r\n    tv = [IGNORE_INDEX] * EPISODE_LENGTH\r\n    for qi, qk in enumerate(gk):\r\n        inp.append(qk); inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49))\r\n        ora.extend(['READ', 'SKIP'])\r\n        tv[150 + qi*2] = gv[qi]\r\n\r\n    return Episode(\r\n        input_ids=torch.tensor(inp, dtype=torch.long),\r\n        oracle_actions=ora,\r\n        target_value_ids=torch.tensor(tv, dtype=torch.long),\r\n        genuine_keys=gk, genuine_values=gv)\r\n\r\nep = generate_episode(0)\r\nprint(f'Episode: {len(ep.input_ids)} tokens, {N_GENUINE} key-value pairs')\r\nprint(f'Sample oracle: {ep.oracle_actions[:8]}')"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":1064,"aggregated":"from dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom typing import List\r\n\r\nN_GENUINE = 20; EPISODE_LENGTH = 170; QUERY_START = 150\r\nIGNORE_INDEX = -100\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass Episode:\r\n    input_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    oracle_actions: List[str]\r\n    target_value_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    genuine_keys: List[int] = None\r\n    genuine_values: List[int] = None\r\n\r\ndef generate_episode(seed=0):\r\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\r\n    gk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    gv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    fk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n    fv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n\r\n    inp, ora = [], []\r\n    # Encode: 100 steps (50 key+value pairs)\r\n    for i in range(100):\r\n        if i % 2 == 0:\r\n            inp.append(gk[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fk[i//2])\r\n            ora.append('PERCEIVE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\r\n        else:\r\n            inp.append(gv[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fv[i//2])\r\n            ora.append('WRITE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\r\n    # Delay: 50 steps\r\n    for _ in range(50):\r\n        inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49)); ora.append('SKIP')\r\n    # Query: 20 steps\r\n    tv = [IGNORE_INDEX] * EPISODE_LENGTH\r\n    for qi, qk in enumerate(gk):\r\n        inp.append(qk); inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49))\r\n        ora.extend(['READ', 'SKIP'])\r\n        tv[150 + qi*2] = gv[qi]\r\n\r\n    return Episode(\r\n        input_ids=torch.tensor(inp, dtype=torch.long),\r\n        oracle_actions=ora,\r\n        target_value_ids=torch.tensor(tv, dtype=torch.long),\r\n        genuine_keys=gk, genuine_values=gv)\r\n\r\nep = generate_episode(0)\r\nprint(f'Episode: {len(ep.input_ids)} tokens, {N_GENUINE} key-value pairs')\r\nprint(f'Sample oracle: {ep.oracle_actions[:8]}')","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1774309511893}}
{"type":"message","id":"dc5f2dce","parentId":"6d98e9c9","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:45:34.175Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The bug is clear. The code builds `inp` which has:\n- 100 encode steps\n- 50 delay steps\n- 20 query steps (10 pairs of 2 = 20 additions to inp)\n\nSo `inp` has `100 + 50 + 20 = 170` items.\n\nBut `tv` is initialized with `[IGNORE_INDEX] * EPISODE_LENGTH` where `EPISODE_LENGTH = 170`. So `tv` has 170 slots.\n\nThen in the query loop:\n```python\nfor qi, qk in enumerate(gk):  # qi goes 0..19\n    inp.append(qk); inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49))  # adds 2 items\n    ora.extend(['READ', 'SKIP'])\n    tv[150 + qi*2] = gv[qi]  # writes to tv[150], tv[152], ..., tv[188]\n```\n\n`tv[150 + qi*2]` where qi goes 0..19 means tv[150], tv[152], ..., tv[188]. \n\nFor qi=19: `150 + 19*2 = 188`. But tv has only 170 items (indices 0..169). So index 188 is way out of range.\n\nThe fix: `EPISODE_LENGTH` should be at least 189, or the `tv` indexing needs to be adjusted. Since the inp length is already correct at 170, `EPISODE_LENGTH` should be larger to accommodate the `tv` indices being written.\n\nLooking at the structure: `QUERY_START = 150`, and `qi*2` means each query writes to even positions starting at 150. With 20 queries, the last write is at position `150 + 19*2 = 188`.\n\nThe simplest fix is `EPISODE_LENGTH = 189` to make `tv` large enough.\n\nBut I'm realizing there's another issue with the structure itself. Each query appends 2 items to `inp` and writes to 1 position in `tv`. If there are 20 queries, that should produce 40 `inp` items, but the current code is trying to write 20 values to `tv` positions that don't exist. Looking at the actual cell output, the sequence is exactly 100 + 50 + 20 = 170 tokens. So the inp list is being built correctly, but I need to figure out why the query loop is trying to write to positions 150-188 when the valid range is only 0-169. The issue is that EPISODE_LENGTH = 170 doesn't 