{"type":"message","id":"9fd0e5e0","parentId":"e33feb39","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:45:49.813Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So the cells are:\n- Cell 0: Title \"# SR-MoE Training\"\n- Cell 1: imports\n- Cell 2: Constants section\n- Cell 3: \"Architecture B (simplified)\"\n- Cell 4: dataclass + generate_episode (this is the problematic one - \"after architecture B\")\n- Cell 5: SRMoETrainer class\n- Cell 6: DEEPSEED = 42\n- Cell 7: Training section (this is the one with the error at line 47, `ep = generate_episode(0)`)\n\nWait, the error says \"Cell In[7], line 47\" and the traceback shows `ep = generate_episode(0)` is at line 47 of cell 7. But based on my output, cell 7 is \"Training\" section with just `DEEPSEED = 42`. That doesn't make sense.\n\n\nLet me reconsider the mapping - maybe the notebook cell indices don't directly correspond to what I'm seeing, or cell 7 was executed in a previous kernel state. I need to look at the actual generate_episode function to understand what's failing. The issue is that EPISODE_LENGTH = 170 but the indexing `tv[150 + qi*2]` goes up to 188, which exceeds the list bounds. I need to either increase EPISODE_LENGTH to 189 or adjust the indexing scheme. Looking at the input sequence length of 170, it seems the episode structure might need a different approach to properly handle the query values being stored. The issue is that `inp` has 170 elements but `tv` needs to be indexed up to 188 for the query values. I should increase `EPISODE_LENGTH` to 190 to accommodate the maximum index `150 + 19*2 = 188`, then verify the cell is properly saved.","thinkingSignature":"523c2baecdf9a446960232b948312867d04e2003b997534175a76db677cf18a6"},{"type":"text","text":"Found it. `EPISODE_LENGTH = 170` but the query loop writes to `tv[150 + qi*2]` where qi goes 0→19, so the last write is to index 188. The `tv` array is too short. The fix is straightforward:\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_function_glch7nxtbf1j_1","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"python -c \"\nimport json\nwith open(r'C:\\dev\\notebooks\\SRMoE_Training.ipynb') as f:\n    nb = json.load(f)\ncell = nb['cells'][4]\nsrc = ''.join(cell['source'])\nprint(src)\n\" 2>&1"}}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":81469,"output":527,"cacheRead":13925,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":95921,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774309535114}}
{"type":"message","id":"534e7883","parentId":"9fd0e5e0","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:45:50.215Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_function_glch7nxtbf1j_1","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"from dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom typing import List\r\n\r\nN_GENUINE = 20; EPISODE_LENGTH = 170; QUERY_START = 150\r\nIGNORE_INDEX = -100\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass Episode:\r\n    input_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    oracle_actions: List[str]\r\n    target_value_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    genuine_keys: List[int] = None\r\n    genuine_values: List[int] = None\r\n\r\ndef generate_episode(seed=0):\r\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\r\n    gk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    gv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    fk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n    fv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n\r\n    inp, ora = [], []\r\n    # Encode: 100 steps (50 key+value pairs)\r\n    for i in range(100):\r\n        if i % 2 == 0:\r\n            inp.append(gk[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fk[i//2])\r\n            ora.append('PERCEIVE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\r\n        else:\r\n            inp.append(gv[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fv[i//2])\r\n            ora.append('WRITE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\r\n    # Delay: 50 steps\r\n    for _ in range(50):\r\n        inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49)); ora.append('SKIP')\r\n    # Query: 20 steps\r\n    tv = [IGNORE_INDEX] * EPISODE_LENGTH\r\n    for qi, qk in enumerate(gk):\r\n        inp.append(qk); inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49))\r\n        ora.extend(['READ', 'SKIP'])\r\n        tv[150 + qi*2] = gv[qi]\r\n\r\n    return Episode(\r\n        input_ids=torch.tensor(inp, dtype=torch.long),\r\n        oracle_actions=ora,\r\n        target_value_ids=torch.tensor(tv, dtype=torch.long),\r\n        genuine_keys=gk, genuine_values=gv)\r\n\r\nep = generate_episode(0)\r\nprint(f'Episode: {len(ep.input_ids)} tokens, {N_GENUINE} key-value pairs')\r\nprint(f'Sample oracle: {ep.oracle_actions[:8]}')"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":361,"aggregated":"from dataclasses import dataclass\r\nfrom typing import List\r\n\r\nN_GENUINE = 20; EPISODE_LENGTH = 170; QUERY_START = 150\r\nIGNORE_INDEX = -100\r\n\r\n@dataclass\r\nclass Episode:\r\n    input_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    oracle_actions: List[str]\r\n    target_value_ids: torch.Tensor\r\n    genuine_keys: List[int] = None\r\n    genuine_values: List[int] = None\r\n\r\ndef generate_episode(seed=0):\r\n    rng = random.Random(seed)\r\n    gk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    gv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(N_GENUINE)]\r\n    fk = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n    fv = [rng.randint(0, 49) for _ in range(60)]\r\n\r\n    inp, ora = [], []\r\n    # Encode: 100 steps (50 key+value pairs)\r\n    for i in range(100):\r\n        if i % 2 == 0:\r\n            inp.append(gk[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fk[i//2])\r\n            ora.append('PERCEIVE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\r\n        else:\r\n            inp.append(gv[i//2] if i//2 < N_GENUINE else fv[i//2])\r\n            ora.append('WRITE' if i//2 < N_GENUINE else 'SKIP')\r\n    # Delay: 50 steps\r\n    for _ in range(50):\r\n        inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49)); ora.append('SKIP')\r\n    # Query: 20 steps\r\n    tv = [IGNORE_INDEX] * EPISODE_LENGTH\r\n    for qi, qk in enumerate(gk):\r\n        inp.append(qk); inp.append(rng.randint(0, 49))\r\n        ora.extend(['READ', 'SKIP'])\r\n        tv[150 + qi*2] = gv[qi]\r\n\r\n    return Episode(\r\n        input_ids=torch.tensor(inp, dtype=torch.long),\r\n        oracle_actions=ora,\r\n        target_value_ids=torch.tensor(tv, dtype=torch.long),\r\n        genuine_keys=gk, genuine_values=gv)\r\n\r\nep = generate_episode(0)\r\nprint(f'Episode: {len(ep.input_ids)} tokens, {N_GENUINE} key-value pairs')\r\nprint(f'Sample oracle: {ep.oracle_actions[:8]}')","cwd":"C:\\Users\\Zwmar\\.openclaw\\workspace"},"isError