{"type":"message","id":"6339df98","parentId":"e377e117","timestamp":"2026-03-23T23:47:23.118Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The fix works. Now input_ids and target_value_ids are both 190 tokens, and the TV non-IGNORE positions are at 150, 152, ..., 188 (20 positions for the 20 query answers).Let me report this to Zach.","thinkingSignature":"f3e51b94ace9864c2ed63564ddc19b5fc5eb3309ecf518b29360b1a700a53cbe"},{"type":"text","text":"Fixed. The bug: `EPISODE_LENGTH = 170` but queries wrote to `tv[150 + qi*2]` where qi goes 0→19, so the last index written was 188 — way past the 170-element array.\n\nChanged `EPISODE_LENGTH` from 170 → 190 in both places (cell 3 constants + cell 4 generate_episode). Now:\n- `input_ids`: 190 tokens ✓\n- `target_value_ids`: 190 tokens ✓  \n- TV non-IGNORE at positions 150, 152, 154 ... 188 (the 20 query answers) ✓\n\nAlso verified: `oracle_actions` correctly starts `['PERCEIVE', 'WRITE', 'PERCEIVE', 'WRITE', ...]` — 100 encode + 50 delay + 40 query steps = 190 actions."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":86054,"output":233,"cacheRead":13925,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":100212,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1774309634691}}
